docs.lead_paragraph: The American Gas and Electric Company and subsidiaries report better than seasonal trends in earnings for July, when gross revenues were $4,601,171, compared with $4,350,934 a year before. In June gross revenues were about $4,519,000, compared with 54,423,000 in the corresponding month of 1932.

docs.lead_paragraph: HAVANA, Aug. 29 -- United States Ambassador Sumner Welles and Treasury Secretary Martinez Saenz conferred today regarding modification of the Cuban-American reciprocity treaty. It was announced that the Treasury Department had named Dr. Roberto A. Netto as Cuban delegate to the commission that will study the treaty, presumably in Washington.

docs.lead_paragraph: College graduates and even college students, as well as industrial workers, on the Pacific Coast, at least, already have cause to bless the NRA. Largely because of the renewed business activity of the past month, jobs have now been found for the majority of last June's graduates of the University of Southern California, its employment bureau reports.

docs.lead_paragraph: MADRID, Sept. 8. -- The government of Premier Manuel Azana collapsed today under the load of reverses in last Sunday's election for members of a Tribunal of Constitutional Guarantees and the gradual disintegration of the parties supporting the government, especially the Radical Socialists and the Federals.

docs.lead_paragraph: THE dramatic developments ow taking place in Cuba have brought a crisis in President Roosevelt's Latin-American policy. Although in certain respects the situation in Cuba is unique, the policy applied by Washington to the Cuban problem may determine our future course toward Latin America as a whole.
